/* Encapsulation
- packaging of complex functionality to make it easier to use in an application.
- Accss to individual functions may be restricted. 
- Encapsulated data may be hidden. 

- Use custom classes to wrap and maintain complex codes. 


Benefits: 
- Breaking functiinality into small, maintainable units 
- Grouping functions and data together
- Supporting testing of software at a granular level
*/
